\nI’m working through coding guidelines here. The instruction “Do not restate deterministic entries” seems to suggest that I shouldn’t repeat dependencies. I’m wondering if the advice to \\\"use javax.servlet APIs\\\" indirectly restates that idea, but it’s still just guidance. I think I should avoid saying “add servlet,” as it might conflict with the intention behind the instruction. I need to keep it clear and consistent while focusing directly on what's necessary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Meaningful coverage of jackrabbit-webdav reaches servlet-facing WebDAV request/response/server APIs, and the artifact declares the servlet API as provided rather than transitive.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The resolved jackrabbit-webdav artifact exposes classes such as DavServletRequest, DavServletResponse, WebdavRequestImpl, and AbstractWebdavServlet that depend on javax.servlet types, while its POM marks servlet-api as provided; the existing 1.5.0 tests already need the same test dependency to compile and exercise these APIs.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, live WebDAV server, environment variable, or system property is indicated. Keep tests in-process with small stub implementations/mocks for WebDAV collaborators rather than starting Jackrabbit or an external WebDAV endpoint. Use the legacy javax.servlet API family, not jakarta.servlet.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The dependency only unlocks servlet-facing API coverage; Native Image may still require metadata fixes for the actual run failure.\",\n    \"The library is old and uses commons-httpclient 3.x and pre-Jakarta servlet APIs, so generated tests should avoid modern jakarta.servlet imports.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_035d2cccadaa885a016a425b4